feat: Drop Python 2 support (#105)

BREAKING CHANGE: This release drops Python 2 support

Django has [dropped Python 2 support](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.2/releases/2.0/#python-compatibility) ever since Django 2.0 (December 2, 2017). With Django 3.0 coming very soon and Python 2 reaching end of life, it doesn't make sense to continue supporting Python 2.

commit.message: docs: add syntax highlighting  (#102)

chore: Use Black to format code (#100)

There's a lot of momentum to using [Black](https://github.com/psf/black). For example, [Django will use it](https://github.com/django/deps/blob/master/accepted/0008-black.rst)

This pulls the bandaid off to avoid mixing lint changes w/ code changes in the future. I opted to not dictate how Black is run because I'm not 100% sure how that should happen. To make sure PRs contributors are following this, I added a lint check in CI.

commit.message:
fix: changelist action links had no 'href' (#98)

I probably copy pasted something wrong and brought an extra arg into the `reverse`, so `reverse` never found anything and the actions in the changelist never rendered with a `href`. This makes the args match the url definition so these buttons work again.

Thanks to @mvbrn for the original fix.

closes #96

commit.message:
Add support for Django 2.0 (#85)

Adding support for Django 2.0+, and removing support for Django versions up to 1.8, the oldest supported LTS release. This allows us to replace the now deprecated django-extensions UUIDField with the Django native version, and drop a couple of other hacks. Resolves #84
